File: The Democratic Alliance (DA) in the Eastern Cape made history on Saturday by successfully concluding South Africa's first-ever virtual political congress. JOHANNESBURG - The Democratic Alliance (DA) in the Eastern Cape made history on Saturday by successfully concluding South Africa's first-ever virtual political congress. Nqaba Bhanga and Andrew Whitfield have both been elected unopposed for additional three-year terms as provincial leader and provincial chairperson respectively. Delegates have also voted to elect two Deputy Provincial Leaders and three Deputy Provincial Chairpersons. READ: DA leadership battle heats up Provincial Leader: Nqaba Bhanga
2 Deputy Provincial Leaders: Chantel King, Bobby Stevenson
Provincial Chairperson: Andrew Whitfield
3 Deputy Provincial Chairpersons: Yusuf Cassim, Vicky Knoetze, Wonga Potwana